1) Fund Stability Score
Use:
	•	Age
	•	AUM
These two are already in your sheet and work well together.
Simple formula

Stability Score = 60% AUM percentile + 40% Age percentile

This rewards:
	•	established funds
	•	trusted funds
	•	higher scale funds
Very common in practical screening systems.


2) Category-wise Peer Rank
Use:
	•	Scheme Category
This is the most important method.
How it works
Rank each fund only within the same Scheme Category.
Example:
	•	all Large Cap funds together
	•	all Flexi Cap funds together
	•	all ELSS funds together
Uses your existing column directly Most fair Must-have for ranking

3) Risk Quality Score
Use:
	•	Sharpe
	•	Sortino
	•	Standard Deviation
This is the strongest ranking block from your dataset.
Simple formula

Risk Quality = 40% Sharpe + 40% Sortino + 20% StdDev(reverse)

Why this is best
It rewards:
	•	higher return per risk
	•	better downside control
	•	lower volatility
This is simple and highly explainable.

